Scholarship for Masters (MS) in USA for Indian Students

  • 85 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jul 07,2023 05:42 PM IST

Higher education abroad has received much more importance as compared to the times when Indian students didn’t travel overseas that much, but now it’s of utmost important to attend a prestigious institution, whether in India or any other country in the world to follow post graduate degrees specifically. This trend also picked up momentum due to ever increasing competition among professional scenarios.

Telegram Whatsapp Facebook Linked In Twitter

Table of Contents

  • • Scholarships for Masters (MS) in USA for Indian Students:
Read More


These days, Indian students travel to various countries for higher studies, and plan their future accordingly. Many countries have some prestigious universities and colleges for admission to post graduate degrees. Among them, USA is the most culturally diverse country with a technological spot called- Silicon Valley. Hence, aspirants can choose to study in USA and experience a culturally diverse community, technological opportunities, exceptional learning experiences, and career opportunities. However, the US education system demands higher tuition fees and cost of living. It is considered the 3rd most expensive nation globally, which requires an average amount of $24,914 as university costs and $11,651 as cost of living annually.

For additional financial help for students in USA, some options are scholarships, fellowships and loans. Meritorious students receive scholarships which could be fully or partially paying. Although it also depends on the level of study, course, and the institution chosen by the applicant. Scholarships are broadly categorized into:

  • Program-specific scholarship
  • Government-funded scholarship
  • Subject-specific scholarships
  • Organization provided

Scholarships for MS in USA is critical for the students who plan to study in the USA. It’s some of the benefits are:

  • Helps academically strong students get a quality education regardless of their financial condition.
  • Students are motivated to study at their maximum potential, securing fantastic job opportunities.
  • A scholarship is not required to be repaid, in case of full settlement, and so it helps reduce debts compared to other university payment options like loans with huge interest rates.

Scholarships for Masters (MS) in USA for Indian Students:

ScholarshipAmount/ Expense Covered (*T&C Apply)
Global study Awards10,000 Pounds
Generation Google Scholarship$1,000 USD
AAUW International Fellowships$20,000 USD

Global Study Awards
Launched by the British Council, this scholarship supports students with exceptionally good IELTS result and are driven to aim and achieve higher. It’s a suitable option for post graduate degree with 10,000 pounds offered for tuition fees. Remaining amount could be allocated as living expenses as well. Student should be 18 years of age and need to produce acceptance letter from university.

Generation Google Scholarship
Google offers this scholarship to assist technologically sound students or aspiring for the same in higher studies. They are offered $1,000 USD and must be a 2nd year student at an accredited university. This is applicable for specifically computer science or computer engineering students, with strong academic performance.

AAUW International Fellowships
It’s one of a kind of scholarship supporting women, to promote equity and education among girls. This scholarship is provided by the American Association of University Women (AAUW) to women who are non – U.S. citizens. This is considered one of the best MS scholarships for women to apply for. $20,000 US are provided covering tuition fee, living expenses and dependent child care.

Fulbright Foreign Student Program
The Fulbright Scholarships Program supports cultural and academic exchange among foreign participants and the U.S. It enables students to research and study in the United States for one year or longer at universities.
 
Narotam Sekhsaria Foundation Scholarships
Established by Mr. Narotam Sekhsaria, this foundation is dedicated to support Indian students for higher studies. It provides interest free loan scholarship for INR 20 lakhs. Indian graduates below age of 30 can receive it after applying for acceptance in the university.

Stanford Reliance Dhirubhai Fellowships
It was established in collaboration by Reliance Industries limited and the Stanford GSB as Reliance Dhirubhai India Education Fund. This scholarship is extended to excelling students and almost 80% of the tuition fee gets covered under it. Also covers living expenses and travel fares. An estimated amount of $83,000 is provided to each one.

TATA Scholarship at Cornell University
Tata Education and development trust has arranged $25 million funding for Cornell to assist Indian student in their pursuit of higher education. Based on certain requirements as TOEFL or IELTS score, admission offer from Cornell and need based financial aid eligibility, it’s a boon for aspiring students.
 
S.N. Bose Scholars Student Exchange Program
It came into conception to honour Professor Satyendra Nath Bose and provides stipend of USD 2000, along with health insurance and airfare. Other than being an Indian student, it is only provided to students with stream of Atmospheric and Earth sciences, Chemical Sciences, Engineering sciences, Mathematical and computational Sciences and Physical Sciences.

Although getting a scholarship for MS in USA can be intimidating for students along with so many decisions already to be taken about University, stream and living conditions, but it is a wise decision to apply for scholarships suitable to respective situation. Hence, this guidance is meant to help students who want to take an informed decision about scholarships and want to utilize their finances in a best manner.

FAQ

How much CGPA score is required for MS in the USA?
Usually GPA score of 7.5-8 is expected to be eligible for further process, but along with better GRE score and a strong SOP, lower score could also be accepted.
What are the basic documents required for applying to scholarship in USA?
A copy of Passport, ID, transcripts, SOP, CV, essay, Test scores, financial information along with tax returns, medical information.
Do Indian students receive a full scholarship to study in the USA?
Some Universities help in covering the complete cost of living in USA as Inlaks scholarship, Tata scholarships and more.
Which elements are important to be mentioned in the scholarship essay to study in USA?
Several important elements like degree of accomplishments, leadership experience, obstacles faced and overcame, learnings from hardships and how it transformed them and any other significant pointer to be mentioned.
Which Universities in USA offer the most number of scholarships to Students?
Some universities as Harvard University, Princeton university, Yale University, MIT etc.
